1
00:00:01,468 --> 00:00:04,869
<i>♪♪ [ Child Humming ]</i>

2
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:11,243
♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪

3
00:00:11,312 --> 00:00:15,113
♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪

4
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:19,218
I FINISHED MY BUILDING.

5
00:00:23,791 --> 00:00:25,857
I'M FINISHED!

6
00:00:30,964 --> 00:00:33,898
THIS ONE'S BEEN WITH US
FOR ONLY 36 HOURS,

7
00:00:33,968 --> 00:00:36,701
AND HE'S ALREADY
DEMONSTRATING MORE TALENT
THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.

8
00:00:36,771 --> 00:00:39,104
HEY!
I'M FINISHED!

9
00:00:42,476 --> 00:00:44,910
HI, JAROD.
I'M SYDNEY.

10
00:00:44,978 --> 00:00:47,846
I'LL BE TAKING CARE OF YOU
FOR A WHILE.
WHY?

11
00:00:47,915 --> 00:00:49,848
WHERE'S MY MOM AND DAD?

12
00:00:51,318 --> 00:00:54,820
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>

13
00:01:41,969 --> 00:01:44,970
MA'AM, THE MATERIALS
ON BOARD ARE
HIGHLY EXPLOSIVE.

14
00:01:45,038 --> 00:01:47,038
SO AM I.

15
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:49,974
I NEVER AGREED
WITH THE COMPANY...

16
00:01:50,044 --> 00:01:51,976
ABOUT FLUSHING OUR TANKS
AT SEA.

17
00:01:52,046 --> 00:01:55,313
I KNEW THOSE CHEMICALS
HAD TO BE DOING SOMETHING NASTY.

18
00:01:55,382 --> 00:01:58,983
YEAH, I'M GLAD
CAPTAIN JAROD
TURNED US IN.

19
00:01:59,053 --> 00:02:01,920
YOU KNOW, I, UH,
KINDA MISS THE GUY.

20
00:02:01,988 --> 00:02:04,923
ALTHOUGH, UH,
HE WAS A LITTLE WEIRD.

21
00:02:04,991 --> 00:02:06,925
[ Chuckles ]

22
00:02:06,993 --> 00:02:10,462
EVERYTHING WITH HIM
WAS ALWAYS "20 QUESTIONS."
AND ALWAYS THE SAME SUBJECT.

23
00:02:10,531 --> 00:02:12,797
- WHICH WAS?
- PEOPLE.

24
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:15,366
<i> THIS BELONG</i>
<i> TO CURIOUS GEORGE?</i>

25
00:02:15,436 --> 00:02:19,537
<i>YEAH. EVERYTHING IS</i>
<i>JUST THE WAY HE LEFT IT.</i>
<i>COMPANY MADE SURE OF THAT.</i>

26
00:02:19,606 --> 00:02:23,875
<i>SAY, ARE YOU PULLIN' MY CORK</i>
<i>ABOUT JAROD NOT REALLY</i>
<i>BEING A CAPTAIN?</i>

27
00:02:23,943 --> 00:02:26,645
THANK YOU FOR YOUR HELP.

28
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:32,150
WHAT IS IT?

29
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:34,152
ARTICLES
ABOUT THAT ALUET VILLAGE...

30
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:37,689
WHERE EVERYONE WAS GETTING SICK
FROM THE CONTAMINATED FISH.

31
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:41,693
HE MUST HAVE BEEN
IN QUITE A HURRY,
LEAVING ALL THIS BEHIND.

32
00:02:41,762 --> 00:02:43,695
IT'S GOT TO BE
INTENTIONAL.

33
00:02:43,764 --> 00:02:45,697
A BREAD CRUMB.

34
00:02:45,766 --> 00:02:47,699
HE'S TRYING
TO KEEP ME CLOSE.

35
00:02:47,768 --> 00:02:50,702
YOUR LITTLE MONSTER
NEEDS HIS TEDDY BEAR,
HUH, SYDNEY?

36
00:02:50,771 --> 00:02:52,704
JAROD IS NOT A MONSTER.

37
00:02:52,773 --> 00:02:55,707
[ Giggles ]
CALL HIM WHAT YOU WANT,
DR. FRANKENSTEIN.

38
00:02:55,776 --> 00:02:57,709
JUST TELL ME WHERE HE IS.

39
00:02:57,778 --> 00:03:00,278
I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS,
MISS PARKER.

40
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:05,250
BUT I'M AFRAID I KNOW
WHAT HE'S UP TO.

41
00:03:06,253 --> 00:03:09,187
<i>[ Woman On P.A.,</i>
<i>  Indistinct ]</i>

42
00:03:09,256 --> 00:03:12,323
SIR, DON'T DO THIS.
LIE DOWN.

43
00:03:14,828 --> 00:03:17,429
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>
<i>[ Phones Ringing ]</i>

44
00:03:24,103 --> 00:03:27,038
[ Man ]
EXCUSE ME. EXCUSE ME.
<i> [ Woman Speaking Greek ]</i>

45
00:03:27,107 --> 00:03:30,041
MY MOTHER'S HERE
FOR HER EXPLORATORY.
YOU'RE IN THE WRONG PLACE.

46
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:32,043
YOU WANT ADMITTING.
[ Continues Speaking Greek ]

47
00:03:32,112 --> 00:03:35,046
SPEAK ENGLISH, HONEY.
SHE WON'T SPEAK ENGLISH.

48
00:03:35,115 --> 00:03:37,715
SHE SAYS SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO BE CUT OPEN.

49
00:03:37,784 --> 00:03:40,418
<i>SHE DOESN'T TRUST DOCTORS.</i>

50
00:03:40,487 --> 00:03:42,287
I DON'T BLAME HER.

51
00:03:42,356 --> 00:03:44,389
<i> [ Nurse ]</i>
<i> END OF THE HALL.</i>

52
00:03:49,029 --> 00:03:51,730
<i> [ Man Shouting ]</i>
<i> SHE SWALLOWED A MARBLE!</i>
<i> B.P.'s 80 OVER 40.</i>

53
00:03:51,799 --> 00:03:54,733
PULSE IS 110.
RAPID AND THREADY.
SHE'S CYANOTIC.

54
00:03:54,801 --> 00:03:57,235
GET DR. SHAPIRO!
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>HE'S IN O.R. 3!</i>

55
00:03:57,304 --> 00:03:59,937
THEN PAGE DR. TRADER!

56
00:04:00,007 --> 00:04:01,707
HOLD ON, SWEETIE.
YOU'LL BE FINE.

57
00:04:01,775 --> 00:04:03,575
NICOLE,
GET E.N.T., STAT!

58
00:04:03,644 --> 00:04:08,079
<i>ALL RIGHT, FELLAS. LET'S GO.</i>
<i>MOVE IT! ONE, TWO, THREE, GO!</i>
<i>DR. TRADER TO O.R. 3!</i>

59
00:04:08,148 --> 00:04:11,049
-<i> [ Paramedic ] GOT IT?</i>
- [ Nurse ]
HYPEREXTEND HER HEAD.

60
00:04:11,117 --> 00:04:13,618
WHERE IS TRADER?
<i>I PAGED HIM.</i>
<i>HE'S NOT ANSWERING!</i>

61
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:18,089
-<i> HER PRESSURE'S FALLING.</i>
-<i> GET ME A THREE-C.C. SYRINGE</i>
<i>  AND A SIZE EIGHT E.T. TUBE.</i>

62
00:04:18,158 --> 00:04:21,593
<i>GET SECURITY</i>
<i>TO GET THIS MAN OUT OF HERE.</i>
<i>WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?</i>

63
00:04:21,661 --> 00:04:24,228
<i> - SHE'S GOING</i>
<i> INTO RESPIRATORY ARREST.</i>
- SHE'S NOT BREATHING.

64
00:04:24,297 --> 00:04:26,998
WOULD YOU LIKE TO
DO THE TRACH?
<i>02 SET RIGHT DOWN.</i>

65
00:04:27,067 --> 00:04:29,668
- PREPARE TO VENTILATE.
- NO! GET SECURITY!

66
00:04:29,737 --> 00:04:32,070
<i> [ Nurse ]</i>
<i> GET A DOCTOR!</i>
I<i> AM</i> A DOCTOR.

67
00:04:33,039 --> 00:04:35,841
<i>[ Officer ]</i>
<i>WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?</i>

68
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:39,344
<i>GWEN?</i>
LEAVE HIM BE.

69
00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:43,648
GIVE ME THE SYRINGE.
REMOVE THE PLUNGER.

70
00:04:46,053 --> 00:04:48,787
<i> GIVE ME THE TOP</i>
<i> OF THE E.T. TUBE.</i>

71
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:52,257
BAG.

72
00:04:53,693 --> 00:04:57,428
[ Air Expelling ]

73
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:03,167
- WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?
- AIR ENTRY ON BOTH SIDES
OF THE CHEST.

74
00:05:03,236 --> 00:05:05,169
<i>SHE'S PINKING UP.</i>

75
00:05:05,238 --> 00:05:08,206
<i>[ Girl Inhaling, Wheezing ]</i>
NOW,<i> THAT'S</i> A NICE SOUND.

76
00:05:24,758 --> 00:05:27,692
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>WELL, I HOPE I DIDN'T CAUSE</i>
<i>TOO MUCH CONFUSION THIS MORNING.</i>

77
00:05:27,761 --> 00:05:29,694
DON'T APOLOGIZE.
YOU SAVED A LIFE.

78
00:05:29,763 --> 00:05:31,696
OH, DR. HENDRICKS.

79
00:05:31,765 --> 00:05:34,699
I NEED YOUR SIGNATURE
ON LINES 10 AND 14, PLEASE.

80
00:05:34,768 --> 00:05:38,202
F.Y.I., RUSSELL,
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING DONE
AROUND HERE, ASK GWEN.

81
00:05:38,272 --> 00:05:41,606
I MAY RUN THIS PLACE,
BUT SHE IS THE BOSS.

82
00:05:42,976 --> 00:05:45,143
<i>[ Gwen ]</i>
<i>THANK YOU.</i>
<i>DOCTORS.</i>

83
00:05:48,648 --> 00:05:51,382
<i> MILES! SORRY. I'M LATE.</i>

84
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:54,385
DR. JAROD RUSSELL,
DR. ALAN TRADER,
CHIEF OF SURGERY.

85
00:05:54,454 --> 00:05:57,889
NICE TO MEET YOU.
I HEAR I MISSED YOU IN ACTION
THIS MORNING, DOCTOR.

86
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:01,492
NEVER SEEN A TRACH LIKE THAT.
IS THAT A NEW PROCEDURE
THEY'RE TEACHING AT HOPKINS?

87
00:06:01,561 --> 00:06:04,862
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I READ IT IN A BOOK.
[ Laughing ]

88
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:10,302
WELL,
WHEREVER YOU LEARNED IT,

89
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:13,305
I APPRECIATE YOU
STANDING IN FOR ME LIKE THAT.

90
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:16,308
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY DAMN BEEPER, BUT...

91
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,310
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

92
00:06:18,378 --> 00:06:20,946
BRAND-NEW.
EVEN TAKES MESSAGES.

93
00:06:21,982 --> 00:06:24,049
PLEASE, SIT DOWN.

94
00:06:25,753 --> 00:06:27,919
<i>WELL, YOUR RECORD AT HOPKINS</i>
<i>WAS IMPECCABLE.</i>

95
00:06:27,988 --> 00:06:30,922
WE ARE HONORED
TO HAVE YOU ON BOARD.

96
00:06:30,991 --> 00:06:35,293
<i>NOT MANY DOCTORS</i>
<i>WITH YOUR CREDENTIALS COME TO</i>
<i>A HOSPITAL AS SMALL AS OURS.</i>

97
00:06:35,362 --> 00:06:37,295
WHY QUEEN OF ANGELS?

98
00:06:37,363 --> 00:06:39,865
WELL, I COULD TELL YOU IT WAS
FOR THE CAREER OPPORTUNITY,

99
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:42,867
BUT THE TRUTH IS,
YOU WERE THE ONLY HOSPITAL
OFFERING STOCK OPTIONS,

100
00:06:42,935 --> 00:06:46,604
<i>AND RUMOR HAS IT YOU MIGHT BE</i>
<i>PURCHASED BY AN H.M.O.</i>

101
00:06:46,673 --> 00:06:49,741
[ Chuckling ]
WE'VE BEEN TALKING
TO SOME PEOPLE.

102
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:52,277
- [ Laughing ]
- DON'T WORRY, RUSSELL.

103
00:06:52,346 --> 00:06:55,680
<i> STICK WITH US,</i>
<i> AND YOU'LL BE DRIVING</i>
<i> A NEW LEXUS IN NO TIME.</i>

104
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:57,682
[ Both Laughing ]

105
00:06:57,751 --> 00:07:01,118
<i>BUT ON TO</i>
<i>MORE IMPORTANT BUSINESS.</i>
<i>DO YOU PLAY RACQUETBALL?</i>

106
00:07:01,187 --> 00:07:03,588
I'VE HEARD OF IT.
<i>GOOD.</i>

107
00:07:03,657 --> 00:07:05,390
GOOD.
WE'LL HAVE A GAME.

108
00:07:05,459 --> 00:07:09,093
<i>WELL, WELCOME</i>
<i>TO QUEEN OF ANGELS.</i>
<i>WE ARE THRILLED TO HAVE YOU.</i>

109
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:11,729
IT'S A PLEASURE TO BE HERE.

110
00:07:14,168 --> 00:07:18,102
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>IMAGINE MY EXCITEMENT AT</i>
<i>BEING RECALLED FROM CORPORATE.</i>

111
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:20,104
<i> ONLY YOU...</i>

112
00:07:20,174 --> 00:07:23,608
COULD HAVE CREATED A MESS
BIG ENOUGH TO PUT ME
BACK IN THE FIELD.

113
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:26,611
I AM THRILLED TO BE
WORKING WITH YOU AS WELL.

114
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,345
<i> HMM.</i>
<i> NOT FOR LONG.</i>

115
00:07:28,414 --> 00:07:30,348
WE'VE TAGGED JAROD'S
ACCOUNT IN ANCHORAGE.

116
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:33,351
HE USES
AN A.T.M. ANYWHERE,
AND HE'S OURS.

117
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:36,354
DON'T UNDERESTIMATE HIM.
IF WE'RE TO CATCH HIM,
WE'LL NEED TO BE PATIENT.

118
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:39,857
LOOK, SYD,
YOU MAY BE SATISFIED
IN YOUR LABORATORY,

119
00:07:39,927 --> 00:07:42,860
PROBING SMALL MINDS
TO SOLVE BIG PROBLEMS.

120
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:46,364
BUT I HAVE CAREER GOALS
THAT DON'T INCLUDE
SCHLEPPING ACROSS COUNTRY...

121
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:48,366
CHASING AFTER
BOY WONDER.

122
00:07:48,435 --> 00:07:51,702
YOU WERE SUCH
A HAPPY LITTLE GIRL.
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

123
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:54,705
[ Beeping ]
I GREW UP, SYDNEY.

124
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:56,774
[ Buzz ]
SO SHOULD YOU.

125
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:05,917
THIS IS
A WASTE OF ENERGY.

126
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:08,920
I'VE BEEN
THROUGH JAROD'S ROOM
A THOUSAND TIMES.

127
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,922
I HAVEN'T.

128
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:14,592
WHAT ARE YOU HOPING TO FIND?
HE LEFT A BREAD CRUMB
ON THE TANKER.

129
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:17,595
AND I'LL BET
HE LEFT ONE HERE.

130
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,664
RUN THE SIM.

131
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:25,036
THIS IS
JAROD'S LAST PROJECT.

132
00:08:25,105 --> 00:08:28,039
WHEN THE BLACK BOX
ON THIS FLIGHT
WASN'T RECOVERED,

133
00:08:28,108 --> 00:08:31,042
HE SIMULATED
THE FINAL MOMENTS
OF THE CRASH.

134
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:33,544
USING HIS INNATE
PRETENDER SKILLS,

135
00:08:33,613 --> 00:08:37,916
JAROD EFFECTIVELY
BECAME EACH MEMBER
OF THE COCKPIT CREW...

136
00:08:37,984 --> 00:08:42,219
AND PINPOINTED
THE CAUSE OF THE CRASH
FOR OUR CLIENT.

137
00:08:42,288 --> 00:08:44,221
HMM.

138
00:08:44,291 --> 00:08:47,224
HELL OF AN ENVIRONMENT
YOU KEEP HIM IN, SYD.

139
00:08:47,294 --> 00:08:50,227
AND WITH INPUT LIKE THIS,
MAYBE WE'LL FIND HIM...

140
00:08:50,297 --> 00:08:52,229
MASQUERADING
AS A POSTAL WORKER.

141
00:08:52,299 --> 00:08:54,766
HE DOESN'T MASQUERADE.
HE'S A PRETENDER.

142
00:08:54,834 --> 00:08:57,735
HMM.
HE BECOMES
ANYTHING HE WANTS TO BE.

143
00:08:57,804 --> 00:09:01,172
WELL, THE CENTRE SHOULD HAVE
STUCK TO COMPUTERS
FOR THEIR SIMULATIONS.

144
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,708
THEY DON'T RUN AWAY.
BUT THEY'RE NOT HUMAN.

145
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:07,712
THEY CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW THE CREW WAS FEELING
AS THE AIRCRAFT LOST POWER,

146
00:09:07,781 --> 00:09:10,214
HOW THEIR EMOTIONS
CONTRIBUTED TO THEIR FATE.

147
00:09:10,283 --> 00:09:12,216
<i>JAROD CAN.</i>

148
00:09:12,285 --> 00:09:14,619
VERY, VERY CLEVER.

149
00:09:14,688 --> 00:09:17,621
- DO YOU KNOW WHAT THIS IS?
- AN ORIGAMI ANGEL.

150
00:09:17,691 --> 00:09:20,357
BUT I HAVEN'T FIGURED OUT
THE EMOTIONAL CONNECTION
TO HIM YET.

151
00:09:20,426 --> 00:09:24,228
IT'S NOT AN ANGEL. ITS WINGS
ARE BENT. IT'S ONISIUS.

152
00:09:25,966 --> 00:09:28,933
THE GREEK GOD OF RETRIBUTION.
HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.

153
00:09:29,002 --> 00:09:32,069
I'M IMPRESSED.
HOW COME YOU KNOW SO MUCH
ABOUT GREEK LORE?

154
00:09:32,138 --> 00:09:35,740
OH, I DID A LOT OF FRAT BOYS
IN COLLEGE.

155
00:09:35,808 --> 00:09:37,742
HERE'S YOUR BREAD CRUMB, SYDNEY.

156
00:09:37,811 --> 00:09:41,479
YOUR SOCIOPATH
THINKS HE IS SOME KIND
OF VIGILANTE...

157
00:09:41,548 --> 00:09:43,881
GETTING EVEN
FOR THE LITTLE GUY.

158
00:09:50,824 --> 00:09:53,858
<i>ST. ANDREW'S MIDDLE SCHOOL,</i>
<i>QUEENS.</i>

159
00:10:07,573 --> 00:10:10,808
<i>♪♪ [ Ice Cream Truck ]</i>

160
00:10:15,581 --> 00:10:18,583
- IT TASTES BETTER
BEFORE IT MELTS.
- OH. RIGHT.

161
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:30,128
THIS IS GOOD!

162
00:10:32,065 --> 00:10:34,265
THIS IS REALLY VERY GOOD!

163
00:10:34,334 --> 00:10:37,268
DO THEY WHIP AIR INTO IT
TO FLUFF IT UP?

164
00:10:37,336 --> 00:10:40,205
I DON'T MAKE IT, PAL.
I JUST SERVE IT.

165
00:10:40,273 --> 00:10:43,274
<i>[ School Bell Rings ]</i>
[ Children Chattering ]

166
00:10:51,685 --> 00:10:53,685
<i> [ Boy ]</i>
<i> COME ON!</i>
<i> SHOOT IT! SHOOT IT!</i>

167
00:10:53,754 --> 00:10:56,755
[ Yells ]
[ Shouting, Chattering ]

168
00:11:31,557 --> 00:11:33,824
<i>[ Car Alarm Blaring ]</i>

169
00:11:33,894 --> 00:11:37,962
NOW THIS IS FASCINATING.
THEY WIN MONEY
BY GUESSING WORD PUZZLES?

170
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:39,964
YOU'VE NEVER SEEN
<i> WHEEL OF FORTUNE?</i>

171
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,999
WHAT ROCK
YOU BEEN LIVING UNDER?

172
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:44,835
UH, I'VE BEEN BUSY.

173
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:48,373
<i> "THE COURTSHIP</i>
<i> OF MILES STANDISH."</i>

174
00:11:48,441 --> 00:11:50,675
<i> [ Loud Whistle ]</i>

175
00:11:50,744 --> 00:11:52,676
HEY!

176
00:11:58,318 --> 00:12:01,219
UH, WE GOT US
A LITTLE SITUATION HERE.

177
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:06,324
UH, THE A.T.M. SAYS
THAT YOUR BANK ACCOUNT
IN ALASKA HAS BEEN FROZEN.

178
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:08,693
NO PUN.
[ Chuckling ]

179
00:12:08,762 --> 00:12:12,497
NOW MAYBE YOU'RE HAPPY,
BUT I'M OUT A BENJY
FOR MY EFFORTS.

180
00:12:12,566 --> 00:12:14,465
DID YOU DO WHAT I ASKED?

181
00:12:14,534 --> 00:12:16,967
MY FRIEND,
IT WAS AN OSCAR-WINNING
PERFORMANCE.

182
00:12:19,605 --> 00:12:23,741
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE GIVING ME A C-NOTE
FOR FINDING OUT YOU'RE BROKE?

183
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:25,643
WE HAD AN AGREEMENT.

184
00:12:25,712 --> 00:12:27,645
HEY, WHATEVER SENDS YOU.

185
00:12:27,714 --> 00:12:30,915
SAY, YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND
ME IF YOU NEED ME, HUH?

186
00:12:49,269 --> 00:12:51,336
<i>[ Knock On Door ]</i>

187
00:12:51,404 --> 00:12:53,404
JUST A SECOND.

188
00:12:59,312 --> 00:13:01,178
COME IN.

189
00:13:01,247 --> 00:13:03,213
GOOD MORNING, DR. RUSSELL.

190
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:06,283
<i>SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,</i>
<i>BUT COULD YOU GO TALK</i>
<i>TO THE GREEK LADY?</i>

191
00:13:06,352 --> 00:13:10,254
<i>SHE YELLS AT EVERYONE</i>
<i>THAT GOES TO HER ROOM. NO ONE</i>
<i>UNDERSTANDS WHAT SHE'S SAYING.</i>

192
00:13:10,323 --> 00:13:12,423
<i> OKAY.</i>
<i> I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.</i>

193
00:13:12,491 --> 00:13:15,092
NICOLE,
DO ME A FAVOR.

194
00:13:15,161 --> 00:13:18,662
HAVE THE LAB
RUN A COMPLETE
DIAGNOSTIC TESTING ON THIS.

195
00:13:18,731 --> 00:13:20,397
AND PUT A RUSH ON IT?

196
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,766
SURE.
<i> THANK YOU.</i>

197
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:24,836
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

198
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:33,611
[ Speaking Greek ]

199
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:37,215
YOU A DOCTOR?

200
00:13:37,283 --> 00:13:39,883
I AM TODAY.
YOU SPEAK ENGLISH.

201
00:13:39,952 --> 00:13:41,885
WHEN I FEEL LIKE IT.

202
00:13:41,954 --> 00:13:44,121
AND I DON'T NEED
NO OPERATION.

203
00:13:46,927 --> 00:13:49,593
- HEY!
- THIS HURTS, DOESN'T IT?

204
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:52,463
HELL YES!

205
00:13:52,532 --> 00:13:54,465
I HAVEN'T GONE FOR WEEKS.

206
00:13:54,534 --> 00:13:56,234
WELL, YOU NEED TO RELAX.

207
00:13:56,302 --> 00:13:58,736
<i>HOW CAN I RELAX</i>
<i>WITH ALL THESE TESTS?</i>

208
00:13:58,805 --> 00:14:00,971
AND NOW THEY WANT TO
CUT ME OPEN.

209
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:04,808
OKAY.
IF YOU DON'T WANT SURGERY,
I'LL CANCEL IT.

210
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:06,811
NO SURGERY?
<i> NO.</i>

211
00:14:06,879 --> 00:14:09,012
I'M GONNA TRY
SOMETHING ELSE.

212
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:11,748
YOU'RE NO DOCTOR.

213
00:14:11,817 --> 00:14:14,652
<i>YOU ARE HUMAN BEING.</i>

214
00:14:14,721 --> 00:14:16,787
<i>MM-HMM.</i>

215
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:21,860
SANDY, MAKE MY DAY.

216
00:14:21,928 --> 00:14:24,929
WELL, WE HAVE
AN A.T.M. HIT ON JAROD'S
ANCHORAGE ACCOUNT.

217
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:27,798
SOME GENIUS.

218
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,601
SATELLITE FEED
SHOULD BE UP IN...
TWO SECONDS.

219
00:14:32,272 --> 00:14:34,205
HE'S IN SANTA FE,
NEW MEXICO.

220
00:14:34,273 --> 00:14:36,707
CALL THE HANGAR
AND GET THE JET READY.

221
00:14:36,776 --> 00:14:40,277
- HOLD IT. HE'S NOT IN SANTA FE.
HE'S IN ROME. NO, LUXEMBOURG.
- CHICAGO, NEW YORK.

222
00:14:40,346 --> 00:14:42,714
THE LITTLE S.O.B.
SCRAMBLED THE A.T.M. SYSTEM.

223
00:14:42,782 --> 00:14:44,649
MIAMI,
PHILADELPHIA,
BARCELONA.

224
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:53,124
HELLO, JAROD.

225
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:01,566
<i>[ Gwen ] YOU CANCELED</i>
<i>MRS. NIKKOS'S SURGERY?</i>
<i>[ Jarod ] YES, I DID.</i>

226
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:05,569
<i> FINE. YOU'RE THE DOCTOR.</i>
<i> AS LONG AS I DON'T</i>
<i> GET BLAMED FOR ANYTHING.</i>

227
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:09,573
AND I WOULD LIKE TO
TRY HER ON AN HERB TEA
CALLED CASSIA SENNA.

228
00:15:09,643 --> 00:15:12,576
DOCTOR, THIS IS QUEENS.
WE DON'T DO TEA.

229
00:15:12,646 --> 00:15:16,080
WE DO NOW.
AND I'D LIKE THE KEY
TO RADIOLOGY, PLEASE.

230
00:15:16,149 --> 00:15:18,582
WELL, ANDY'S
OUT TO LUNCH, BUT--

231
00:15:18,652 --> 00:15:21,085
I KNOW.
THERE YOU ARE.

232
00:15:21,154 --> 00:15:23,087
THANK YOU.

233
00:15:23,156 --> 00:15:25,089
HI!
HI, MAMA!

234
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:27,992
HOW YOU DOIN',
LITTLE SUGAR BABY?

235
00:15:32,198 --> 00:15:34,198
GUESS WHAT IT IS.

236
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:37,368
<i>[ Gwen ]</i>
<i>I'M HOPING FOR TUNA FISH</i>
<i>OR PEANUT BUTTER.</i>

237
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:50,514
I COULD USE A HAND WITH THESE.
THAT IS, IF YOU HAVE ONE FREE.

238
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:52,683
- OH, GOD. IT'S DR. RUSSELL.
-<i> [ Andy ] DR. RUSSELL?</i>

239
00:15:52,753 --> 00:15:54,552
I'M NEW.

240
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:56,954
I'M, UH, EMBARRASSED.

241
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:03,060
BUT, UM, ALWAYS, UH--
ALWAYS HAPPY TO HELP, DOC.

242
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:05,062
[ Clears Throat ]

243
00:16:05,132 --> 00:16:07,232
UH, NOW--

244
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,234
UH, I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

245
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:11,236
KEVIN BAILEY
IS DR. TRADER'S PATIENT.

246
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:13,237
ANY SPECIAL REASON
YOU'RE LOOKING AT THESE?

247
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,240
<i>ANY SPECIAL REASON</i>
<i>THAT YOU'RE IN HERE</i>
<i>HALF NAKED?</i>

248
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:18,810
I CAN BE FORGETFUL
IF YOU CAN.

249
00:16:20,413 --> 00:16:22,346
ALL RIGHT.

250
00:16:22,415 --> 00:16:24,348
YOUR PROBLEM
IS RIGHT HERE...

251
00:16:24,417 --> 00:16:26,350
AT THE T-EIGHTH.

252
00:16:26,419 --> 00:16:29,353
THE EIGHTH THORACIC VERTEBRAE
WAS CRUSHED,
SEVERING HIS SPINAL CORD.

253
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:31,956
KID NEVER HAD A CHANCE.
THAT I UNDERSTAND.
BUT LOOK HERE.

254
00:16:32,024 --> 00:16:34,959
THIS IS THE PRE-OP,
AND THIS IS
THE POST-OP X-RAY.

255
00:16:35,027 --> 00:16:37,629
YEAH.
BUT BOTH OF THEM
ARE IDENTICAL.

256
00:16:37,697 --> 00:16:40,631
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?
IT'S NOT.

257
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:44,168
SOMEONE MUST HAVE MADE
A DUPLICATE
OF THE POST-OP X-RAY.

258
00:16:44,237 --> 00:16:46,403
<i>YOU SEE THAT FOGGING</i>
<i>IN THE CORNER THERE?</i>

259
00:16:46,472 --> 00:16:49,540
THE OLD PROCESSOR
WE KEEP IN THE BASEMENT
DOES THAT.

260
00:16:49,609 --> 00:16:52,744
I SPILLED SOME SODA ON IT WHEN
I FIRST STARTED WORKING HERE.

261
00:16:53,746 --> 00:16:55,679
THE NEW PROCESSOR'S
FOG-FREE.

262
00:16:55,749 --> 00:16:59,517
<i> WHY WOULD SOMEONE MAKE</i>
<i> A COPY OF A POST-OP X-RAY</i>
<i> AND LABEL IT PRE-OP?</i>

263
00:16:59,586 --> 00:17:02,186
MAKES YOU WONDER.

264
00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:13,864
[ Young Jarod ]
I'M ON THE LAST
FLIGHT OF STAIRS,

265
00:17:13,934 --> 00:17:16,367
TERRIFIED OF WHAT
I'M ABOUT TO DO.

266
00:17:16,436 --> 00:17:19,370
MY HEART'S POUNDING.
MY HANDS ARE SWEATING.

267
00:17:19,438 --> 00:17:22,539
<i>I CAN HARDLY HOLD ON</i>
<i>TO THE PACKAGE I TOLD</i>
<i>EVERYONE WAS CURTAIN RODS.</i>

268
00:17:24,077 --> 00:17:28,012
SYDNEY, IS IT POSSIBLE FOR KIDS
TO FORGET THEIR PARENTS?

269
00:17:28,081 --> 00:17:30,014
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>KEEP YOUR MIND FOCUSED, JAROD.</i>

270
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:32,183
<i>CONCENTRATE</i>
<i>ON THE SIMULATION.</i>

271
00:17:35,755 --> 00:17:37,688
AS I NEAR THE WINDOW,

272
00:17:37,757 --> 00:17:41,826
I CAN HEAR THE SOUNDS
OF THE CROWD RISING FROM BELOW.

273
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:44,328
[ Young Jarod ]
I CAN SEE THEM COMING.

274
00:17:44,397 --> 00:17:47,232
HOW FAST ARE THEY GOING?
FORTY MILES PER HOUR.
YOU KNOW THAT.

275
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,233
MY MOUTH'S DRY.

276
00:17:49,302 --> 00:17:51,636
MY HANDS
ARE SHAKING.

277
00:17:51,704 --> 00:17:55,139
I RAISE
THE MANNLICHER CARBINE.

278
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:58,576
I CAN'T FIRE ENOUGH SHOTS
BEFORE THE CAR GOES
UNDER THE OVERPASS.

279
00:17:58,644 --> 00:18:00,878
I CAN'T.
I CAN'T DO THIS ALONE.

280
00:18:00,947 --> 00:18:02,880
HE WASN'T ALONE.

281
00:18:02,949 --> 00:18:04,915
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> HE HAD TO HAVE HAD HELP.</i>

282
00:18:04,984 --> 00:18:08,119
TRADER WASN'T ALONE EITHER,
SYDNEY.

283
00:18:08,188 --> 00:18:10,188
[ Exhales ]

284
00:18:15,995 --> 00:18:18,662
[ Grunts, Laughs ]

285
00:18:18,732 --> 00:18:20,998
[ Gasps ]
GOOD ONE.

286
00:18:22,869 --> 00:18:24,802
[ Exhales ]

287
00:18:24,871 --> 00:18:27,237
GOOD GAME.
[ Panting ]

288
00:18:32,745 --> 00:18:35,679
DON'T LET IT BOTHER YOU.
HE NEVER LETS ANYONE WIN.

289
00:18:35,748 --> 00:18:37,881
[ Jarod Laughs ]
AT LEAST JAROD'S
COMPETITIVE.

290
00:18:37,951 --> 00:18:40,384
HE'S YOUNG.
AND YOU'RE LAZY.

291
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:44,054
YEAH, WELL,
THERE IS THAT.
[ Both Laughing ]

292
00:18:49,829 --> 00:18:52,763
CALSIX.
YOU HAVE A HEART PROBLEM?

293
00:18:52,832 --> 00:18:55,766
<i> MILES IS</i>
<i> A TYPE-A TIME BOMB.</i>

294
00:18:55,835 --> 00:18:59,269
TWO HEART ATTACKS.
ONE MORE,
AND IT'S BYPASS TIME.

295
00:18:59,338 --> 00:19:01,839
WHICH IS WHY
I PLAY RACQUETBALL.

296
00:19:01,907 --> 00:19:03,908
AND I NEED A REFILL.

297
00:19:03,977 --> 00:19:05,642
SO DO I. UM--

298
00:19:05,711 --> 00:19:07,945
<i>IT'S MY DAY OFF.</i>

299
00:19:08,014 --> 00:19:11,749
YOU EXERCISE YOUR WAY,
I'LL EXERCISE MINE.
[ Chuckles ]

300
00:19:11,818 --> 00:19:15,753
<i>-SO, JAROD, DOES QUEEN OF ANGELS</i>
<i> GET A PASSING GRADE?</i>
<i>-ABSOLUTELY.</i>

301
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:19,657
FRANKLY, I EXPECTED THERE
TO BE MORE FALLOUT FROM
THE MALPRACTICE PROBLEMS.

302
00:19:19,725 --> 00:19:22,493
<i> WELL, UNFORTUNATELY,</i>
<i> THAT'S THE COST</i>
<i> OF DOING BUSINESS.</i>

303
00:19:22,562 --> 00:19:26,664
WE'VE HAD OUR DIFFICULTIES,
BUT I WOULD PUT QUEEN OF ANGELS'
RECORD UP AGAINST ANY HOSPITAL.

304
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:30,001
<i>ARE YOU SURE THERE'S</i>
<i>NO HIDDEN LAND MINES,</i>
<i>EVEN WITH THE KEVIN BAILEY CASE?</i>

305
00:19:30,069 --> 00:19:33,170
<i> WELL, THAT WAS A TRAGEDY,</i>
<i> BUT LET'S FACE IT--</i>

306
00:19:33,239 --> 00:19:36,273
AN ORPHANED BOY IN A WHEELCHAIR
MAKE FOR SENSATIONAL HEADLINES.

307
00:19:36,343 --> 00:19:37,975
IT WAS A DAMNED WITCH HUNT.

308
00:19:38,044 --> 00:19:41,645
<i>YES. ONCE THE FRENZY DIED DOWN,</i>
<i>THE TRUTH TOOK OVER,</i>
<i>AND WE WERE EXONERATED.</i>

309
00:19:41,714 --> 00:19:43,781
THAT IS ALL BEHIND US NOW.

310
00:19:46,853 --> 00:19:48,786
<i>[ School Bell Rings ]</i>

311
00:19:48,855 --> 00:19:51,855
<i> [ Shouting, Chattering ]</i>

312
00:19:55,794 --> 00:19:58,229
GET SERIOUS.
IT'S GOOD.

313
00:19:58,297 --> 00:20:03,300
HASN'T ANYONE EVER TOLD YOU?
YOU TALK TO STRANGERS,
YOU END UP ON MILK CARTONS.

314
00:20:04,337 --> 00:20:06,337
MY NAME'S JAROD.

315
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:10,374
IT TASTES BETTER
BEFORE IT MELTS.

316
00:20:12,245 --> 00:20:15,246
YOUR HANDS
STILL CRAMP UP
WHEN YOU WHEEL?

317
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:18,783
WHAT WOULD YOU KNOW
ABOUT IT?

318
00:20:18,851 --> 00:20:21,052
I HAVE A GOOD IMAGINATION.

319
00:20:26,292 --> 00:20:29,226
<i> [ Kids Screaming,</i>
<i> Shouting, Chattering ]</i>

320
00:20:30,430 --> 00:20:32,430
[ Sighs ]

321
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:35,633
IT'S GONNA
GET BETTER.

322
00:20:35,702 --> 00:20:37,635
<i>[ Car Horn Honks ]</i>

323
00:20:37,704 --> 00:20:39,704
I PROMISE.

324
00:20:55,621 --> 00:20:58,556
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>SIR, THERE'S A SHREVE HARMON</i>
<i>CALLING ON LINE SEVEN.</i>

325
00:20:58,624 --> 00:21:02,226
SHREVE<i> AND</i> HARMON BUILT
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

326
00:21:03,763 --> 00:21:06,497
PUT HIM THROUGH
AND TRACE THE CALL.

327
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:09,534
[ Buzz ]

328
00:21:11,638 --> 00:21:13,571
[ Chuckling ]

329
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,573
VERY CLEVER, JAROD.

330
00:21:15,642 --> 00:21:17,575
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

331
00:21:17,644 --> 00:21:20,044
I'M BROKE.
YOU FROZE MY BANK ACCOUNT.

332
00:21:20,113 --> 00:21:22,379
I MUST HAVE JUST MISSED YOU
IN CINCINNATI.

333
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:24,381
THE FLOWERS
WERE STILL FRESH.

334
00:21:24,451 --> 00:21:27,885
WELL, MY PARENTS HAVE BEEN
DEAD FOR 30 YEARS. I FIGURED
IT WAS TIME I SAID GOOD-BYE.

335
00:21:27,954 --> 00:21:29,887
I WANT YOU TO COME HOME.
[ Chuckles ]

336
00:21:29,956 --> 00:21:32,390
THERE'S AN INTERESTING WAY
TO PUT IT-- "HOME."

337
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:35,392
WHY DID YOU LEAVE?
YOU'RE THE SHRINK,
SYDNEY.

338
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:37,895
YOU WANT THE TRUTH?

339
00:21:37,964 --> 00:21:40,397
IT'S BECAUSE OF THE LIES.

340
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:42,399
YOUR LIES.

341
00:21:42,469 --> 00:21:44,935
WHAT LIES?

342
00:21:45,004 --> 00:21:49,841
I FOUND OUT THE REAL APPLICATION
OF MY SIMULATIONS, SYDNEY.

343
00:21:49,909 --> 00:21:52,610
SOUTH PACIFIC
FLEET SIMULATION 118.

344
00:21:52,679 --> 00:21:56,747
YOU TOOK MY RESULTS
AND BLEW A SHIP
OUT OF THE WATER.

345
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:59,616
A HUNDRED AND 33 PEOPLE
WERE ON BOARD.

346
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,753
MY OUTBREAK SIMULATION?

347
00:22:02,822 --> 00:22:05,389
YOU USED IT IN THE FIELD.

348
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:09,393
FORTY-SIX PEOPLE DIED
OF THE EBOLA VIRUS, SYDNEY.

349
00:22:09,462 --> 00:22:14,431
SIMULATION 27.
SIMULATION 16.
SIMULATION 42.

350
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,402
JAROD, THESE WERE
MILITARY CONTRACTS.

351
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:21,405
I HAD NO WAY
OF FINDING OUT ABOUT
THEIR ULTIMATE APPLICATION.

352
00:22:21,474 --> 00:22:24,408
HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED
BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?

353
00:22:24,477 --> 00:22:27,411
YOU NEED TO COME HOME.

354
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,413
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

355
00:22:29,482 --> 00:22:33,617
I'VE BEEN WALKING
AROUND YOUR ROOM,
AND IT FEELS... EMPTY.

356
00:22:35,054 --> 00:22:37,488
WELL, I CAN'T SAY
I MISS IT.

357
00:22:37,557 --> 00:22:39,490
AND BY THE WAY,

358
00:22:39,559 --> 00:22:42,325
ICE CREAM<i> IS</i> GOOD.

359
00:22:43,429 --> 00:22:45,829
JAROD,
THIS IS GETTING SERIOUS.

360
00:22:45,899 --> 00:22:48,099
- THEY BROUGHT IN MISS PARKER.
- UH-OH.

361
00:22:48,167 --> 00:22:50,567
WELL, YOU BETTER
WATCH YOUR BACK TOO, SYDNEY.

362
00:22:50,636 --> 00:22:54,371
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING, JAROD?
-USING THE SKILLS YOU TAUGHT ME.

363
00:23:08,854 --> 00:23:11,054
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>I'M COMPLETELY LOCKED OUT HERE.</i>
<i>I GOT NOTHIN'.</i>

364
00:23:11,123 --> 00:23:14,091
<i>ARE YOU GETTING ANYTHING?</i>
<i>NO. LET ME TRY</i>
<i>A NEW ACCESS CODE.</i>

365
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:17,094
TALK TO ME.
WE'VE BEEN LOCKED OUT.

366
00:23:17,163 --> 00:23:21,132
OUR CLIENT HIRED US
TO SEE IF THE STOCK EXCHANGE
WAS VULNERABLE TO MANIPULATION.

367
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:25,135
JAROD SPENT FOUR MONTHS
ON THIS SIMULATION.
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

368
00:23:25,204 --> 00:23:27,704
THE CLIENT GAVE US FIVE MILLION
TO TEST JAROD'S RESULTS.

369
00:23:27,773 --> 00:23:30,307
<i> JAROD KNEW TODAY</i>
<i> WAS THE DAY OF THE TEST.</i>

370
00:23:30,375 --> 00:23:33,977
<i>EVERYTHING WAS GOING TO PLAN</i>
<i>UNTIL SOMEONE ON THE FLOOR</i>
<i>STARTED TO MANIPULATE MARKETS.</i>

371
00:23:34,046 --> 00:23:36,714
-<i> THEY'VE STOLEN</i>
<i> OUR FIVE MILLION.</i>
- GEE.

372
00:23:36,782 --> 00:23:38,715
I WONDER WHO THAT COULD BE.

373
00:23:38,784 --> 00:23:40,818
WELL, AT LEAST
WE KNOW WHERE HE IS.

374
00:23:57,970 --> 00:23:59,903
[ Laughing ]

375
00:23:59,973 --> 00:24:02,840
THAT'S SOME KIND MEDICINE
YOU GOT THERE.

376
00:24:02,908 --> 00:24:06,844
I MIGHT LAUGH MYSELF DEAD
BEFORE I POOP!

377
00:24:06,912 --> 00:24:09,847
[ Chuckling ]
LAUGHTER IS
VERY GOOD MEDICINE.

378
00:24:09,915 --> 00:24:11,983
AND SO IS
REFLEXOLOGY.

379
00:24:12,051 --> 00:24:14,986
NICOLE,
MASSAGE THESE MARKS,
WOULD YOU, PLEASE?

380
00:24:15,054 --> 00:24:16,988
THANKS.

381
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:19,156
YOU GONNA
TELL ME THE TRUTH?

382
00:24:20,159 --> 00:24:22,093
WHAT TRUTH?

383
00:24:22,161 --> 00:24:25,663
A MAN WHO GIVES ME THE SUN,

384
00:24:25,731 --> 00:24:27,664
WHO MASSAGES MY FEET,

385
00:24:27,733 --> 00:24:30,400
WHO GIVES ME
STINKY TEA--

386
00:24:32,071 --> 00:24:34,071
WHO ARE YOU?

387
00:24:37,076 --> 00:24:40,310
OH, SO MUCH SADNESS.

388
00:24:40,379 --> 00:24:42,379
AND SO MUCH JOY.

389
00:24:51,991 --> 00:24:54,925
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>COMFORTING TO KNOW THERE ARE</i>
<i>ONLY 137 HOSPITALS...</i>

390
00:24:54,994 --> 00:24:57,728
IN THE METROPOLITAN
NEW YORK AREA.

391
00:24:57,797 --> 00:24:59,630
YOUR ROOMS
HAVE BEEN PREPAID,
MISS PARKER.

392
00:24:59,698 --> 00:25:02,333
- PREPAID?
- IN CASH.

393
00:25:02,401 --> 00:25:05,569
AND THE GENTLEMAN
LEFT THIS.

394
00:25:09,675 --> 00:25:12,309
NOT A WORD.

395
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:19,950
ALAN. HEY.
JAROD, HI. HI.

396
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:22,953
DENISE, I'LL HAVE
ANOTHER GINGER ALE,
PLEASE.

397
00:25:23,022 --> 00:25:25,689
MAKE THAT TWO
GINGER ALES.
OKAY.

398
00:25:26,725 --> 00:25:28,658
EITHER YOU'VE
JUST BEEN MUGGED,

399
00:25:28,727 --> 00:25:31,161
OR IT'S BEEN
ONE HELL OF A SHIFT.

400
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:34,164
FOUR GUNSHOT WOUNDS,
A LOBECTOMY
AND A RUPTURED SPLEEN,

401
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,233
AND I'M ONLY
HALFWAY THROUGH.

402
00:25:37,436 --> 00:25:41,505
ALAN, I THINK I MIGHT HAVE
SCREWED UP TODAY.

403
00:25:41,573 --> 00:25:43,573
REALLY SCREWED UP.

404
00:25:45,077 --> 00:25:47,511
HEY, HOW YOU DOIN'?
YEAH, I'M OKAY.

405
00:25:47,580 --> 00:25:50,013
HEY, LOOK,
IS THIS TRADER'S EXCHANGE?

406
00:25:50,083 --> 00:25:54,084
GOOD. LOOK, I GOTTA
GET A MESSAGE TO HIM. YEAH.

407
00:25:54,152 --> 00:25:56,787
SO,

408
00:25:56,856 --> 00:25:58,990
WHAT'S THE TROUBLE?

409
00:26:02,194 --> 00:26:06,630
THE LOBECTOMY?
I THINK I LEFT A HEMO INSIDE
WHEN I SEWED HER UP.

410
00:26:06,699 --> 00:26:09,266
NO PROBLEM.
NO PROBLEM?

411
00:26:09,335 --> 00:26:12,469
YOU THINK THAT'S GONNA
MAKE THE H.M.O. HAPPY?
CHECK HER CHART.

412
00:26:12,538 --> 00:26:15,339
IF THE WHITE COUNT
IS SPIKED,
YOU'VE FOUND YOUR HEMO.

413
00:26:15,408 --> 00:26:17,207
WELL, THEN WHAT?

414
00:26:17,276 --> 00:26:19,543
TAKE IT OUT.

415
00:26:19,612 --> 00:26:22,179
TELL HER YOU FOUND
SOME INTERNAL BLEEDING.

416
00:26:22,248 --> 00:26:24,181
HEY, YOU'RE THE DOCTOR.
OH.

417
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:26,851
<i>[ Pager Beeping ]</i>
AH.

418
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:30,554
ALWAYS COUNT ON IT HAPPENING
ON YOUR LUNCH BREAK, HUH?

419
00:26:36,028 --> 00:26:38,962
UM, I GOTTA GET BACK.

420
00:26:39,031 --> 00:26:42,032
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR THE ADVICE, ALAN.
<i> YEAH.</i>

421
00:27:26,278 --> 00:27:28,612
<i> [ Typing On Keyboard ]</i>

422
00:27:34,587 --> 00:27:36,720
<i>[ Knock On Door ]</i>

423
00:27:36,789 --> 00:27:38,955
- [ Beeps ]
- COME IN.

424
00:27:39,024 --> 00:27:41,392
OH, GOOD.
YOU'RE STILL HERE.

425
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:43,894
<i>THE LAB REPORT</i>
<i>ON THAT BLOOD WORKUP</i>
<i>YOU ASKED FOR.</i>

426
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:45,996
- THANK YOU.
- SURE.

427
00:27:47,299 --> 00:27:49,299
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

428
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:04,814
THIS ONE'S BEEN WITH US
FOR ONLY 36 HOURS,

429
00:28:04,884 --> 00:28:08,151
AND HE'S ALREADY
DEMONSTRATING MORE TALENT
THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.

430
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:10,220
HEY!
I'M FINISHED!

431
00:28:16,395 --> 00:28:18,261
HI, JAROD.
I'M SYDNEY.

432
00:28:18,330 --> 00:28:21,265
I'LL BE TAKING CARE OF YOU
FOR A WHILE.
WHY?

433
00:28:21,333 --> 00:28:23,333
WHERE'S MY MOM AND DAD?

434
00:28:24,403 --> 00:28:27,003
<i>WHERE'S MY MOM AND DA--</i>
<i>[ Clicks Off ]</i>

435
00:28:27,072 --> 00:28:29,507
[ Horn Blasting ]

436
00:28:29,575 --> 00:28:31,842
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>PLEASE EVACUATE THE BUILDING.</i>

437
00:28:31,910 --> 00:28:34,845
<i>[ Alarm Blaring ]</i>
KEEP MOVING.
PLEASE REMAIN CALM.

438
00:28:34,914 --> 00:28:36,847
THANK YOU.

439
00:28:36,916 --> 00:28:39,850
SYDNEY. DOWNSTAIRS.
PLEASE MAKE YOUR WAY
TO THE EMERGENCY EXITS.

440
00:28:39,919 --> 00:28:42,352
THIS WAY.
<i> [ Woman ]</i>
<i> WAIT UP FOR ME.</i>

441
00:28:42,421 --> 00:28:45,021
<i>[ Alarm Continues Blaring ]</i>
JUST ONE MINUTE, SIR.

442
00:28:45,090 --> 00:28:48,826
<i>[ Female Voice ] PLEASE</i>
<i>EXIT YOUR ROOM AND PROCEED</i>
<i>TO THE NEAREST STAIRWAY EXIT.</i>

443
00:28:48,895 --> 00:28:51,661
MY GOD.

444
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,663
SORRY TO WAKE YOU,
SYDNEY,

445
00:28:53,733 --> 00:28:56,100
BUT I NEEDED
TO SPEAK TO YOU
FACE-TO-FACE.

446
00:28:56,168 --> 00:28:58,402
YOU LOOK WELL.

447
00:28:59,771 --> 00:29:01,505
WHAT'S THIS?

448
00:29:01,574 --> 00:29:04,508
INSTRUCTIONS FOR RETRIEVING
THE CENTRE'S FIVE MILLION.

449
00:29:06,445 --> 00:29:08,378
LESS MY COMMISSION.
[ Chuckles ]

450
00:29:08,447 --> 00:29:12,449
DON'T LOOK SO SURPRISED.
I DON'T WANT MONEY.
I WANT THE TRUTH.

451
00:29:12,517 --> 00:29:14,385
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

452
00:29:14,453 --> 00:29:17,254
WHO AM I?
DID THE CENTRE ADOPT ME?

453
00:29:17,323 --> 00:29:21,624
WAS I BOUGHT, OR WAS I STOLEN?
AND WHERE ARE MY MOM AND DAD?

454
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:24,127
JAROD, WE'VE BEEN OVER THIS
A THOUSAND TIMES.

455
00:29:24,197 --> 00:29:26,797
YOUR PARENTS DIED
IN A PLANE CRASH.

456
00:29:26,866 --> 00:29:31,034
YES, I KNOW THE STORY, SYDNEY.
IT'S BEEN BURNED INTO MY BRAIN
FOR 30 YEARS.

457
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:34,538
BUT, YOU SEE,
I DID A LITTLE CHECKING.

458
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:38,375
THERE'S THIS GENETIC ANOMALY
THAT'S IN MY BLOOD...

459
00:29:38,444 --> 00:29:41,245
THAT SHOULD BE
IN MY SUPPOSED PARENTS.

460
00:29:41,314 --> 00:29:43,246
BUT IT'S NOT.

461
00:29:43,315 --> 00:29:46,950
THEREFORE, IT'S IMPOSSIBLE
THAT I'M THEIR SON.

462
00:29:47,953 --> 00:29:50,888
SO, THE TRUTH, FOR ONCE.

463
00:29:50,957 --> 00:29:53,390
[ Man ]
I THOUGHT YOU QUIT.
[ Miss Parker ] SHUT UP.

464
00:29:53,459 --> 00:29:55,459
WHERE WERE YOU GOING,
SYDNEY?

465
00:29:58,730 --> 00:30:00,664
DAMN IT!
WHAT?

466
00:30:00,732 --> 00:30:03,067
NO SMOKE!
OUT OF MY WAY!

467
00:30:04,069 --> 00:30:06,002
I'M SORRY, JAROD.

468
00:30:06,072 --> 00:30:09,073
I DIDN'T KNOW.
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.

469
00:30:10,509 --> 00:30:12,443
BUT IT DOESN'T MATTER.

470
00:30:12,511 --> 00:30:14,445
IT MATTERS TO ME.

471
00:30:14,513 --> 00:30:18,014
I AM NOT GONNA BE
YOUR LITTLE SCIENCE EXPERIMENT
ANYMORE, SYDNEY.

472
00:30:19,385 --> 00:30:22,018
I CAN BE
ANYTHING I WANT TO BE.
YOU TRAINED ME WELL.

473
00:30:22,088 --> 00:30:25,021
I CAN BE A DOCTOR.
I CAN BE AN ENGINEER.
I CAN BE AN ASTRONAUT!

474
00:30:25,091 --> 00:30:27,023
AND SO MUCH MORE!

475
00:30:27,092 --> 00:30:29,693
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHO I AM!

476
00:30:29,761 --> 00:30:32,262
TELL ME WHO I AM.
I DON'T KNOW EITHER.

477
00:30:32,331 --> 00:30:35,432
AT THE TIME,
I HAD NO REASON TO QUESTION
WHAT THE CENTRE TOLD ME.

478
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:37,434
I SWEAR.
THEN PROVE IT.

479
00:30:37,503 --> 00:30:40,437
GIVE ME TOMORROW'S CODE
TO THE CENTRE'S MAINFRAME.

480
00:30:40,506 --> 00:30:43,240
THE TRUTH ABOUT WHO I AM
HAS TO BE IN THERE.

481
00:30:43,309 --> 00:30:47,310
YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT.
SYDNEY,
YOU STOLE MY LIFE!

482
00:30:48,581 --> 00:30:50,580
PLEASE GIVE IT BACK TO ME.

483
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:54,784
<i> SYDNEY! SHOOT HIM!</i>

484
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:56,786
7-5-1-2. GO.

485
00:30:56,855 --> 00:30:58,655
<i> [ Gunshot ]</i>
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> NO! NO GUNS!</i>

486
00:30:58,724 --> 00:31:00,724
LET ME GO!
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

487
00:31:03,362 --> 00:31:05,362
[ Grunting ]

488
00:31:08,434 --> 00:31:10,367
MAKE UP YOUR MIND,
SYDNEY!

489
00:31:10,436 --> 00:31:13,036
BE A SCIENTIST
OR A MOMMY!

490
00:31:13,105 --> 00:31:15,105
YOU CAN'T BE BOTH!

491
00:31:24,450 --> 00:31:26,883
<i>[ Man On P.A. ]</i>
<i>YOUR ATTENTION, PLEASE.</i>
<i>[ Train Horns Blowing ]</i>

492
00:31:26,952 --> 00:31:29,887
<i>FINAL CALL</i>
<i>FOR ALL PASSENGERS DEPARTING</i>
<i>ON THE ATLANTIC SPECIAL...</i>

493
00:31:29,955 --> 00:31:31,889
<i>TO WASHINGTON, D.C....</i>

494
00:31:31,957 --> 00:31:35,058
<i>WITH STOPS IN TRENTON,</i>
<i>PHILADELPHIA AND BALTIMORE.</i>

495
00:31:35,127 --> 00:31:38,295
<i>NOW BOARDING ON PLATFORM 12.</i>
<i>ALL ABOARD, PLEASE.</i>

496
00:31:39,298 --> 00:31:41,731
EXCUSE ME.
GWEN.

497
00:31:41,801 --> 00:31:43,801
GWEN!

498
00:31:45,037 --> 00:31:47,971
DR. RUSSELL.
CAN I SPEAK TO YOU
FOR A MINUTE?

499
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:50,040
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

500
00:31:54,646 --> 00:31:57,080
YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO HAVE THAT.

501
00:31:57,149 --> 00:31:59,583
I KNEW THAT TRADER
WAS INVOLVED.

502
00:31:59,651 --> 00:32:02,719
WHAT I COULDN'T FIGURE OUT
WAS WHY WOULD ANYBODY
HELP HIM COVER IT UP?

503
00:32:02,788 --> 00:32:04,722
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

504
00:32:04,790 --> 00:32:08,158
I DIDN'T EITHER,
UNTIL I FOUND THIS.

505
00:32:08,227 --> 00:32:10,393
IT'S A PRINTOUT
OF YOUR RECORD.

506
00:32:10,462 --> 00:32:12,963
WHO ELSE KNEW
YOU WERE IN PRISON
BESIDES TRADER?

507
00:32:14,199 --> 00:32:16,266
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

508
00:32:16,335 --> 00:32:19,469
SOMEONE THAT DOESN'T THINK
WHAT HAPPENED
TO KEVIN BAILEY'S FAIR.

509
00:32:19,538 --> 00:32:21,804
A-AND YOU THINK I<i> DO?</i>

510
00:32:21,873 --> 00:32:25,809
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT IT TOOK
FOR ME TO GET BACK ON MY FEET.

511
00:32:25,878 --> 00:32:28,445
<i>I'VE GOT A JOB.</i>

512
00:32:28,514 --> 00:32:32,048
I'VE GOT A GOOD MAN.
I'VE GOT A BEAUTIFUL BABY BOY.

513
00:32:32,117 --> 00:32:34,117
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE THEM.

514
00:32:34,186 --> 00:32:36,119
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO LOSE ANYTHING.

515
00:32:36,188 --> 00:32:38,622
<i> JUST TELL THE TRUTH.</i>

516
00:32:38,690 --> 00:32:42,626
WHAT WOULD YOU DO
IF YOUR WIFE CAME HOME
AND TOLD YOU...

517
00:32:42,694 --> 00:32:46,463
THAT SHE'D BEEN A CRACKHEAD
AND A CONVICT?

518
00:32:46,532 --> 00:32:48,965
<i> I'D SAY</i>
<i> SHE PAID HER DEBT.</i>

519
00:32:49,034 --> 00:32:53,202
AND I'D ASK HER WHY
SHE DIDN'T TRUST ME ENOUGH
TO TELL ME THE TRUTH.

520
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:57,541
AT LEAST THAT'S WHAT
I THINK I WOULD DO.

521
00:32:58,777 --> 00:33:01,711
YOU DON'T KNOW
HOW SCARED I AM.

522
00:33:03,047 --> 00:33:04,681
I THINK I DO.

523
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:19,730
I HAD TO PAGE DR. TRADER
THAT NIGHT AT THE SILVER RAIL.

524
00:33:20,999 --> 00:33:23,066
<i>WE ALL KNEW HE DRANK,</i>

525
00:33:23,135 --> 00:33:25,068
BUT NOBODY WANTED TO ADMIT IT.

526
00:33:25,137 --> 00:33:27,070
I SHOWED HIM THE X-RAYS.

527
00:33:27,139 --> 00:33:30,073
EVEN I KNEW THAT THE BOY
SHOULD HAVE BEEN STABILIZED,

528
00:33:30,142 --> 00:33:32,542
BUT HE INSISTED
I WAS WRONG AND--

529
00:33:32,611 --> 00:33:35,245
HE WAS THE DOCTOR.

530
00:33:37,249 --> 00:33:41,251
HE SEVERED
THE LITTLE BOY'S SPINAL CORD
WHEN HE MOVED HIM.

531
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:46,289
<i>BUT IT WAS DR. HENDRICKS</i>
<i>WHO COVERED IT ALL UP...</i>

532
00:33:46,358 --> 00:33:50,159
<i>AND THREATENED TO EXPOSE MY PAST</i>
<i>IF I DIDN'T GO ALONG.</i>

533
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:52,161
SEE, UH,

534
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:54,798
WHEN TRADER REALIZED
WHAT HE'D DONE,

535
00:33:54,867 --> 00:33:58,402
HE GAVE ME THE PRE-OP X-RAYS
AND TOLD ME TO BURN THEM.

536
00:33:58,470 --> 00:34:00,403
<i>BUT I COULDN'T.</i>

537
00:34:00,472 --> 00:34:02,672
<i>I WENT</i>
<i>TO DR. HENDRICKS INSTEAD.</i>

538
00:34:02,741 --> 00:34:05,675
I DON'T KNOW WHY I THOUGHT
IT WOULD DO ANY GOOD.

539
00:34:05,744 --> 00:34:08,511
HE'S BEEN COVERING FOR TRADER
FOR YEARS.

540
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:10,513
HE TOOK THE X-RAYS,

541
00:34:10,582 --> 00:34:14,183
AND HE MADE ME SWEAR
THAT I WOULDN'T TELL ANYBODY
THAT HE HAD 'EM.

542
00:34:14,253 --> 00:34:17,254
HE SAID THAT HE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO USE THEM FOR INSURANCE.

543
00:34:21,126 --> 00:34:23,059
[ Sighs ]

544
00:34:23,128 --> 00:34:25,595
THANK YOU.

545
00:34:27,232 --> 00:34:30,167
DR. HENDRICKS
ISN'T GONNA GIVE YOU THAT FILM.

546
00:34:30,235 --> 00:34:33,370
HE'D RATHER DIE
THAN RISK THAT HOSPITAL SALE.

547
00:34:38,276 --> 00:34:41,210
DR. TRADER.
ALAN?
IT'S JAROD.

548
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:43,713
WE NEED TO TALK.
ABOUT WHAT?

549
00:34:43,782 --> 00:34:45,715
UH, NOT ON THE PHONE.

550
00:34:45,784 --> 00:34:50,119
CAN YOU MEET ME TODAY
AT THE SILVER RAIL AT NOON?

551
00:34:50,188 --> 00:34:52,222
I'LL BE THERE.
THANKS, ALAN.

552
00:34:54,292 --> 00:34:56,326
<i> [ Punching Keypad ]</i>

553
00:34:59,865 --> 00:35:01,832
MILES.
JAROD RUSSELL.

554
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:04,401
JAROD.
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

555
00:35:04,469 --> 00:35:06,470
HOW ABOUT ANOTHER GAME
OF RACQUETBALL?

556
00:35:06,538 --> 00:35:10,006
WHY WOULD YOU WANT ANOTHER GAME
SO SOON AFTER I CRUSHED YOU?

557
00:35:10,075 --> 00:35:13,342
[ Chuckles ]
TO RETURN THE FAVOR.
HOW ABOUT TODAY AT NOON?

558
00:35:13,411 --> 00:35:15,478
WELL, IT'S YOUR FUNERAL.

559
00:35:15,547 --> 00:35:17,513
WELL, WE ALL HAVE TO GO
SOMETIME.

560
00:35:24,489 --> 00:35:27,424
[ Groans ]
POINT, GAME, MATCH.

561
00:35:27,492 --> 00:35:29,426
TOSS ME MY WATER, WILL YA?

562
00:35:29,494 --> 00:35:31,428
SURE, MILES.

563
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:34,130
<i>[ Hendricks Grunting ]</i>

564
00:35:34,199 --> 00:35:37,200
<i>GEEZ.</i>
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

565
00:35:38,537 --> 00:35:41,471
SO, JAROD,
WHY THE SELF-TORTURE?

566
00:35:41,540 --> 00:35:44,474
WELL, I FIGURE I LET YOU
WIN A FEW GAMES,

567
00:35:44,543 --> 00:35:47,978
I EARN YOUR PITY,
YOU CUT ME
A BETTER STOCK OPTION.

568
00:35:48,046 --> 00:35:50,247
WELL, MY PITY
DOESN'T COME CHEAP.

569
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:57,353
I'LL TELL YOU SOMETHING--
YOU RAN ME ALL OVER THAT COURT.
YOU ARE GETTING BETTER.

570
00:35:57,422 --> 00:35:59,689
I'VE BEEN PRACTICING.
<i>AH.</i>

571
00:36:03,562 --> 00:36:05,495
BUT I WON.

572
00:36:05,564 --> 00:36:09,032
[ Gasping, Panting ]

573
00:36:09,101 --> 00:36:11,301
YOU OKAY, MILES?

574
00:36:11,370 --> 00:36:14,203
JAROD--

575
00:36:14,272 --> 00:36:16,206
[ Gasping ]

576
00:36:16,274 --> 00:36:18,141
MILES?

577
00:36:21,180 --> 00:36:23,179
CAN SOMEBODY
CALL AN AMBULANCE?

578
00:36:24,315 --> 00:36:27,250
DR. RUSSELL SAYS
HE'S RUNNING A BIT LATE.

579
00:36:27,318 --> 00:36:30,253
SHOW ME A DOCTOR
WHO ISN'T, HUH?

580
00:36:30,321 --> 00:36:33,256
I'LL HAVE
ANOTHER QUICK ONE.

581
00:36:33,324 --> 00:36:35,324
<i>SURE.</i>

582
00:36:45,771 --> 00:36:48,705
GET O.R. 3 SET.
DR. HENDRICKS IS HAVING
A HEART ATTACK.

583
00:36:48,774 --> 00:36:50,707
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>WATCH YOUR BACK!</i>

584
00:36:50,776 --> 00:36:53,709
PULSE IS 112 AND THREADY.
B.P. HAS DROPPED
FROM 75 TO 60.

585
00:36:53,778 --> 00:36:58,114
I WANT YOU TO START HIM
ON A NITRO DRIP AND GET HIM
PREPPED FOR SURGERY, STAT!

586
00:37:03,188 --> 00:37:05,121
YOU LIED TO ME.

587
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:09,459
LAST NIGHT, YOU TOLD ME
JAROD CAME HERE TO RETURN
THE FIVE MILLION.

588
00:37:09,528 --> 00:37:12,863
ALL HE REALLY WANTED
WAS THE MAINFRAME CODE.
<i>IT WAS THE LEAST I COULD DO.</i>

589
00:37:12,931 --> 00:37:16,065
HE WAS LIED TO
ABOUT HIS PARENTS.
SO WAS I.

590
00:37:16,134 --> 00:37:18,067
STOP POUTING.

591
00:37:18,137 --> 00:37:21,070
IT WAS NEED-TO-KNOW.
YOU DIDN'T.

592
00:37:21,140 --> 00:37:24,907
ANYWAY, YOU'VE DONE US ALL
A GREAT FAVOR.
YOU SEE, I TAGGED JAROD'S FILE.

593
00:37:24,976 --> 00:37:27,310
HE LOGGED ON THIS MORNING.
WHERE IS HE?

594
00:37:27,378 --> 00:37:32,082
QUEEN OF ANGELS HOSPITAL.
THEY'RE BRINGING THE CAR
AROUND NOW. LET'S GO.

595
00:37:32,150 --> 00:37:33,950
THE CENTRE
WANTS HIM ALIVE.

596
00:37:34,019 --> 00:37:35,885
PREFERABLY.

597
00:37:35,954 --> 00:37:38,455
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>

598
00:37:40,992 --> 00:37:44,995
MILES, WE WERE UNABLE
TO BRING IN A CARDIOLOGIST
FAST ENOUGH.

599
00:37:45,063 --> 00:37:48,464
BUT DON'T WORRY.
I PAGED DR. TRADER.

600
00:37:48,533 --> 00:37:50,633
NO--

601
00:37:50,702 --> 00:37:52,335
HE'LL TAKE CARE
OF YOU, MILES.

602
00:37:52,404 --> 00:37:54,837
- HE TOOK CARE OF KEVIN BAILEY.
- NO.

603
00:37:54,907 --> 00:37:57,007
[ Gasping ]
PLEASE.

604
00:37:57,075 --> 00:37:59,308
YOU DO THE OPERATING.

605
00:37:59,377 --> 00:38:02,445
OKAY, OKAY--
O-OKAY, MILES.
NO PROBLEM.

606
00:38:03,815 --> 00:38:05,748
BUT FIRST,

607
00:38:05,817 --> 00:38:08,751
YOU TELL ME
WHERE KEVIN BAILEY'S
PRE-OP X-RAYS ARE.

608
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:10,953
[ Continues Gasping ]

609
00:38:14,926 --> 00:38:18,595
BEHIND THE PUNJAB PAINTING
IN MY OFFICE.

610
00:38:18,663 --> 00:38:22,098
NOW, YOU DO
THE OPERATION, JAROD.

611
00:38:22,167 --> 00:38:25,101
I-I-I'D LIKE TO, MILES.
I REALLY WOULD.

612
00:38:25,170 --> 00:38:27,103
BUT THAT WOULDN'T
BE ETHICAL.

613
00:38:27,172 --> 00:38:29,105
YOU SEE,

614
00:38:29,174 --> 00:38:31,508
I'M NOT REALLY A DOCTOR.

615
00:38:31,576 --> 00:38:34,010
AND YOU'RE NOT REALLY
HAVING A HEART ATTACK.

616
00:38:34,079 --> 00:38:36,245
TRADER, HE'S ALL YOURS.

617
00:38:37,348 --> 00:38:39,282
OKAY.

618
00:38:39,350 --> 00:38:41,284
LET'S DO THIS.

619
00:38:41,352 --> 00:38:43,620
[ Wheezing ]
JAROD. JAROD--

620
00:38:49,361 --> 00:38:52,295
[ Miss Parker ]
WE'LL START ON THE FIRST FLOOR
AND WORK OUR WAY UP.

621
00:38:52,364 --> 00:38:54,630
JAROD DOES NOT LEAVE.

622
00:38:58,236 --> 00:39:00,169
NICOLE?

623
00:39:00,238 --> 00:39:03,940
WOULD YOU PAGE SECURITY
AND HAVE THEM STOP
DR. TRADER FROM OPERATING?

624
00:39:04,009 --> 00:39:06,643
HE'S DRUNK.
OH, MY GOD!

625
00:39:06,712 --> 00:39:08,645
YEAH.

626
00:39:08,713 --> 00:39:10,714
YOU TAKE THAT SIDE.

627
00:39:24,229 --> 00:39:26,228
JAROD!

628
00:39:47,452 --> 00:39:50,786
<i>GUESS WHAT.</i>
<i> GUESS WHAT I DID TODAY!</i>

629
00:39:51,857 --> 00:39:54,591
OH!
WELL, THAT'S GREAT!

630
00:39:56,194 --> 00:39:58,194
SORRY.

631
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:05,034
HE'S GOT TO BE
IN ONE OF THESE ROOMS.

632
00:40:05,103 --> 00:40:07,036
<i> [ Mrs. Nikkos Screams ]</i>

633
00:40:07,105 --> 00:40:09,105
LET'S GO!

634
00:40:11,176 --> 00:40:14,110
<i> HEY! A MAN!</i>
<i> HE RAN OUT</i>
<i> THE FIRE ESCAPE!</i>

635
00:40:14,179 --> 00:40:16,012
HE'S HEADING TO THE ROOF!

636
00:40:22,387 --> 00:40:24,854
[ Speaks Greek ]
<i>[ Mrs. Nikkos Laughs ]</i>

637
00:40:26,224 --> 00:40:28,524
[ Speaks Greek ]

638
00:40:43,875 --> 00:40:45,641
JAROD!

639
00:41:47,973 --> 00:41:49,906
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>
<i>YOUR ATTENTION, PLEASE.</i>

640
00:41:49,975 --> 00:41:54,077
<i>FLIGHT 1428 TO SAN DIEGO</i>
<i>WILL BE DEPARTING FROM GATE 12.</i>

641
00:41:54,145 --> 00:41:57,146
<i>PLEASE HAVE YOUR</i>
<i>BOARDING PASSES READY.</i>

642
00:41:58,649 --> 00:42:01,384
YOU'D BETTER BOARD, SIR.
YOU DON'T WANNA
MISS THE FLIGHT.

643
00:42:01,453 --> 00:42:03,018
DON'T WORRY.

644
00:42:04,089 --> 00:42:06,923
THEY'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE
WITHOUT ME.

645
00:42:51,535 --> 00:42:52,601
[ Mews ]

